oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Paul Doran crossing Cherry Creek
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Paul Doran, a circuit preacher for the Presbyterian Church, crossing Cherry Creek in a horse-drawn buggy.
He served five churches and oversaw the building of three stone churches modeled after Irish churches.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
